Algorithm: Cheapest Flight Within K Stops

Input values:-
n:number of cities
flights:edges(u->v,cost)
src:starting city
dst:destination area
k:maximum stops allowed

Steps:-
1. Initialize the distances
-Create array dist[] with size value=n
-Set all values to infinity
-Set dist[src]=0

2. Relax edges upto (k+1) times

3. For each iteration:
-Set temp= dist
-For every flight(u,v,cost):
(a) If dist[u]!=infinity:
        update: temp[v]=min(temp[v],dist[u]+cost)
(b) Replace dist=temp

4. If dist[dst]==infinity  -->  return -1
    Else --> return dist[dst]

// Time Complexity:- O(k*E)
-We run the outer loop (k + 1) times
-Inside each loop, we traverse all flights (edges)

// Space Complexity:- O(n)
-dist array → size n
-temp array → size n
